<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About WebNote</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="icon" href="/img/webnotelogo.png">

</head>
<body class="about-body">
  <header>
    <nav>
      <div class="container">
        <a href="/" class="logo">
          <img src="/img/webnotelogo.png" alt="WebNote logo" width="15%">
        </a>
        <ul class="nav-links">
          <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="/users/about">About</a></li>
          <% if (user) { %>
            <li><a href="/profile">Profile</a></li>
            <li>
              <form action="/users/logout" method="POST" style="display: inline;">
                <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>">
                <button type="submit" class="btn-link">Logout</button>
              </form>
            </li>
          <% } else { %>
            <li><a href="/users/login">Login</a></li>
            <li><a href="/users/register">Register</a></li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="about-container">
    <section>
      <h1>About WebNote</h1>
      <img src="/img/webnotelogo.png" alt="WebNote logo" width="15%">
      <p class="about-box">WebNote is a site dedicated to creating, edit, and organize notes into
         categories or folders. WebNote provides a free, fully functional,
         ad-free, responsive, and intuitive interface. Where most alternatives
         are locked behind a subscription paywall and/or are riddled with ads,
         WebNote provides a clutterless alternative. Most of the “free” apps
         similar to the service we provide also have very limited use built-in
         to them in order to persuade users to purchase their subscription based
         service.</p>
      <p class="about-box">
        WebNote enables users to be able to write online notes, edit, save, sort,
        customize, and store those notes in various folders for organization. Notes 
        can then be viewed and edited at any time or place. Your notes will be tamper
        proof and only available to you, ad free, anytime!
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>


  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <p>&copy; 2025 CS346 Project. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
